worldDungeonM.name: Let's Start Exploring!
worldDungeonM.description: Let's start exploring on a server close to your farm.

worldDungeonM.name: In the Warehouse
worldDungeonM.description: Looks like this server controls a warehouse. Those rampaging Digimon have really messed it up!

worldDungeonM.name: Restore the Warehouse!
worldDungeonM.description:
Let's see, to restore the warehouse data...
Oh, no, the Digimon are attacking!

worldDungeonM.name: Trouble in the Gymnasium
worldDungeonM.description: This server controls a gymnasium... Huh? Why is it so noisy in there?!

worldDungeonM.name: A Training Brawl?!
worldDungeonM.description: This isn't a workout, it's a rampage! If they keep it up, they'll destroy the facility data!

worldDungeonM.name: Chill Out, Cyclonemon!
worldDungeonM.description: The coach, Cyclonemon, has gone wild! You might have a little trouble calming him down...

worldDungeonM.name: Swirling Data
worldDungeonM.description: This server controls the air conditioning. Wow, thatâ€™s a lot of  data bytes swirling around!

worldDungeonM.name: Ductwork Jungle
worldDungeonM.description:
This air duct data is as tangled as a jungle...
There might be vicious Digimon lurking inside.

worldDungeonM.name: Out of the Jungle...
worldDungeonM.description: We finally restored the data. Let's pacify the rest of those Digimon!

worldDungeonM.name: Water World
worldDungeonM.description: Up next is this server! It maintains water quality by analyzing data.

worldDungeonM.name: Stagnant Water
worldDungeonM.description: The water data in this server was damaged. At this rate, it could contaminate the water in the real world!

worldDungeonM.name: Mage Rampage
worldDungeonM.description: Sorcermon keeps disrupting the data. If we don't stop him, we'll be stuck fixing it forever!

worldDungeonM.name: Gears of the Assembly Line
worldDungeonM.description:
This area controls a factory.
Oh no! The Hagurumon are rampaging around again!

worldDungeonM.name: Practical Magic
worldDungeonM.description:
Physical attacks don't do much against Digimon on this server...
Let's focus on magic instead!

worldDungeonM.name: The Great Management Domain
worldDungeonM.description: Turbine control data is here, assembly line data is over there. This is the biggest server yet!

worldDungeonM.name: Now What...?
worldDungeonM.description: All component data is restored! Now, I wonder what will come out?

worldDungeonM.name: A Glassed-In World
worldDungeonM.description: This server controls a greenhouse. Hmm... The climate controls are on full blast, aren't they?

worldDungeonM.name: Watch Out for Poison!
worldDungeonM.description: Looks like there are a lot of poisonous Digimon in here. Be careful!

worldDungeonM.name: The Jolly Greenhouse Giant
worldDungeonM.description: Ahh! Cyclonemon is on a rampage!

worldDungeonM.name: Master of the Greenhouse Server?
worldDungeonM.description: That same Cyclonemon is rampaging again! It's like he thinks he's the master of this server!

worldDungeonM.name: Drilling for Data
worldDungeonM.description: This server controls an oil field. There's data welling up all over the place like crude oil!

worldDungeonM.name: Crude Oil Clusters
worldDungeonM.description: Hey, maybe I'll strike it rich! -ahem- Just kidding. Let's restore this server!

worldDungeonM.name: Cluster Competition
worldDungeonM.description: Some of those rampaging Digimon are gathering up Clusters. Is something controlling them?

worldDungeonM.name: Oil Field Offenders
worldDungeonM.description: What are they doing on an oil field server, anyway? Do they just like oil fields?

worldDungeonM.name: Flickering Fish Tank
worldDungeonM.description: This server controls an aquarium. I'd love to say there's nothing wrong with it, but...

worldDungeonM.name: Shelly Secrets
worldDungeonM.description: Looks like Syakomon has a hard, protective shell. A skill that lowers Defense might crack it!

worldDungeonM.name: Deep in the Data
worldDungeonM.description: There's a lot of seaweed and stone data mixed up in here. The kind that Digimon often hide in!

worldDungeonM.name: Leftover Fragments
worldDungeonM.description:
That should do it... Huh? Looks like there are some data bytes left.
Let's find them!

worldDungeonM.name: A Stitch in Time
worldDungeonM.description:
This server controls time.
Huh? Is it just me, or is that second hand moving strangely?

worldDungeonM.name: How Many Digimon?
worldDungeonM.description:
I think I see eight Digimon. No, nine...
Ugh... I can't tell them apart from the clockwork...

worldDungeonM.name: The Wind-Up Clock
worldDungeonM.description: This is data from a windup clock. The data for the spring is broken, so let's repair it!

worldDungeonM.name: A Flock of Clocks
worldDungeonM.description: Sundials, cuckoo clocks, hourglasses, digital watches... So many different kinds of clock!

worldDungeonM.name: Sound the Alarm
worldDungeonM.description:
I think I hear an alarm going off...
Woah! There's a horde of Digimon attacking!

worldDungeonM.name: A Sleepy Skirmish
worldDungeonM.description:
This server controls a park...
Wow, I feel sleepy all of a sudden...

worldDungeonM.name: Scared to Sleep
worldDungeonM.description: -yawn- It looks like some of the Digimon here have Sleep skills...

worldDungeonM.name: Wide Awake
worldDungeonM.description: Digimon that fall asleep are totally helpless. We'll be in trouble if we don't hurry up and win!

worldDungeonM.name: The Ruined Park
worldDungeonM.description: The park data was destroyed while we were asleep. I'm still sleepy... But I'll do my best!

worldDungeonM.name: Patch Up The Park
worldDungeonM.description: Data restoration complete for the grass, the fountains, and the benches. We're almost there!

worldDungeonM.name: Farming Domain
worldDungeonM.description: It looks like the farm data isn't flowing properly to the Digital World. We'd better fix it!

worldDungeonM.name: A Herd of Digimon
worldDungeonM.description: A flock of sheep? No! It's a herd of Digimon!

worldDungeonM.name: Piles of Pastures
worldDungeonM.description: Wow, that's a lot of pasture data! Let's buckle down and restore it!

worldDungeonM.name: Rebuild the Silo!
worldDungeonM.description: This is data from a silo. If we don't restore it, the poor cows and sheep will be in trouble!

worldDungeonM.name: Holy Cow!
worldDungeonM.description: The cows in the real world are mooing in distress. It's udder chaos out there!

worldDungeonM.name: Start the Screening
worldDungeonM.description: Data for film soundtracks and projector lights. This must be the movie theater server!

worldDungeonM.name: Main Titles
worldDungeonM.description: The movie's starting! Those rowdy Digimon are blocking the view. Hey, down in front!

worldDungeonM.name: Protect the Popcorn!
worldDungeonM.description: Popcorn and movies go perfectly together, but something is wrong with the popping sound data!

worldDungeonM.name: A Heart-Pounding Climax
worldDungeonM.description: The movie's getting to the best part! Quick, let's gather these Clusters and restore it.

worldDungeonM.name: Closing Credits
worldDungeonM.description: The credits are rolling in the real world. Let's wrap up our restoration of this server, too.

worldDungeonM.name: A World of Fun
worldDungeonM.description: Cheerful music and shouts of fun. This server must control an amusement park.

worldDungeonM.name: Rumble of the Roller Coaster
worldDungeonM.description: This Cluster is data from a roller coaster... You can almost still hear the shrieks of the people on board!

worldDungeonM.name: Whirling Merry-Go-Round
worldDungeonM.description: This is data from a merry-go-round. Wow! What cute horses! Can we ride it when it's restored?

worldDungeonM.name: Tremendous Teacups
worldDungeonM.description:
This is data from the spinning teacups.
Just looking at it makes me want a ride. Now I'm dizzy!

worldDungeonM.name: The Ferris Wheel at Night
worldDungeonM.description:
Ah, a glittering ferris wheel under the stars.
They're spoiling the mood! Let's fix it, quick!

worldDungeonM.name: The Vast Night Sky
worldDungeonM.description:
Wow! The night sky is so beautiful!
Wait... This is no time for stargazing!

worldDungeonM.name: The Star Digimon
worldDungeonM.description:
That star is so big and bright!
Woah! It's not a star! It's a Starmon!

worldDungeonM.name: Shooting Stars
worldDungeonM.description: Those Clusters are flying around like shooting stars. Now I want to make a wish!

worldDungeonM.name: Sparkling Constellations
worldDungeonM.description: It looks like this is constellation data. We've got to protect the starry night sky!

worldDungeonM.name: Light of the North Star
worldDungeonM.description: SuperStarmon has the Cluster of the North Star! Let's take it back.

worldDungeonM.name: Dark Clusters
worldDungeonM.description:
I'm analyzing these Clusters,
but all the data is pitch-black for some reason...

worldDungeonM.name: A Limestone Cave of Data
worldDungeonM.description: Let me adjust the brightness... Aha! Now I see it! This is data from a limestone cave.

worldDungeonM.name: Inside the Cave
worldDungeonM.description: The Digimon here seem strong against Darkness. Maybe it's because they live in a cave?

worldDungeonM.name: The Spirit of Exploration
worldDungeonM.description: Doing this restoration makes me feel like I'm exploring a cave, too!

worldDungeonM.name: A Data Dead-End
worldDungeonM.description: It looks like this part of the cave is a dead end. I wonder what's inside?

worldDungeonM.name: Hum of the Generators
worldDungeonM.description: This server controls a power plant!

worldDungeonM.name: Scattering Sparks
worldDungeonM.description: All this data fragmentation is causing problems with the turbines. Let's restore it, quick!

worldDungeonM.name: Power Plants and Attributes
worldDungeonM.description:
Lots of enemies here use Thunder attacks. 
I'd bring Digimon strong against Electric and Earth!

worldDungeonM.name: Turbine Repairs
worldDungeonM.description: Now, let's run the restored program. That ought to fix the broken turbines, too!

worldDungeonM.name: Power Up!
worldDungeonM.description: The restoration is finally done! Let's pacify these Digimon so the generators can start up.

worldDungeonM.name: Into the Woods
worldDungeonM.description: It looks like this area controls a forest. Be careful not to get lost!

worldDungeonM.name: Walking Trees
worldDungeonM.description: Cherrymon and Woodmon look just like ordinary trees. They're very tricky, so watch out!

worldDungeonM.name: Dense Forest
worldDungeonM.description: This data is all snarled up with overgrowth. I'll do my best here, too...

worldDungeonM.name: Can't See the Wood for the Trees
worldDungeonM.description: Battling these Digimon is important, but keep training your own Digimon to get stronger, too!

worldDungeonM.name: Howling in the Forest
worldDungeonM.description: It sounds like something is howling out there... Let's go find out what it is!

worldDungeonM.name: The Bakery Entrance
worldDungeonM.description: This is a bakery server, full of delicious bread.

worldDungeonM.name: It Looks Delicious, But...
worldDungeonM.description: Seeing these Clusters reminds me of the data of that yummy bread. Hey, you can't eat Clusters!

worldDungeonM.name: Fire Up the Stove!
worldDungeonM.description: The Clusters in this area are the control data for a stove. Ugh... Now I'm hungry!

worldDungeonM.name: Stovepipe Secrets
worldDungeonM.description: These Clusters are data from a stovepipe, but I can't restore them. Is it some Digimon's fault?

worldDungeonM.name: Baked to Perfection?
worldDungeonM.description: The restoration is almost complete! Take down that boss, but try not to get burnt to a crisp!

worldDungeonM.name: A Pool of Clusters
worldDungeonM.description: This server is flooded with swirling Clusters. Pretty typical for a server that controls a pool.

worldDungeonM.name: Swimming Digimon
worldDungeonM.description: These enemy Digimon are all strong swimmers. Is it because the Cluster data is forming a pool?

worldDungeonM.name: Now, Turn!
worldDungeonM.description: The pool server restoration is halfway complete. I feel like we just executed a perfect turn!

worldDungeonM.name: Off the Diving Board
worldDungeonM.description: Next is the diving board data. You're not really diving in, so keep calm and fight on, okay?

worldDungeonM.name: Poolside Patch-Up
worldDungeonM.description: Once I restore the poolside, this server will be done. I wish I could play in the pool, too...

worldDungeonM.name: Sunday Quest v1.0
worldDungeonM.description:
Even a Rookie can clear this at Max Level!
Go and grab some Light Digivolution Fuel!

worldDungeonM.name: Sunday Quest v2.0
worldDungeonM.description:
If you're training a Champion, you can clear this!
Go and grab some Light Digivolution Fuel!

worldDungeonM.name: Sunday Quest v3.0
worldDungeonM.description:
You'll need this Digivolution Fuel
to Digivolve an Ultimate!
Do your best to grab some!

worldDungeonM.name: Sunday Quest v4.0
worldDungeonM.description: Be sure to prepare with Resistance Upgrades and attacks that strike at Attribute weak points!
